<title>Lateinische Synonyme und Etymologien</title>
                <note>
<p>GRADUALLY</p>
<p>paulatim refers to gradual motion or development under the image of an imperceptible progress.</p>
<p>paulatim refers to such motion or development as happening little by little.</p>
<p>gradatim refers to such development as the result of deliberate slow progress.</p>
                </note>
